HEADWORD: Metrograph
<hw>Met"ro*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ measure
+ <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument attached to a locomotive
for recording its speed and the number and duration of its
stops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metrological</ent>⟦br⟧
